quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  36,33,"There is a sign for them in the dead earth: We give it life, producing grain from it for them to eat"
  36,34,"And We have placed in it gardens of palm trees and grapevines, and caused springs to gush forth in it"
  36,35,"so that they may eat from its fruit, which they had no hand in making. Will they not then give thanks"
  36,36,"Glory be to the One Who created all ˹things in˺ pairs—˹be it˺ what the earth produces, their genders, or what they do not know"
  36,37,"There is also a sign for them in the night: We strip from it daylight, then—behold!—they are in darkness"
  36,38,"The sun travels for its fixed term. That is the design of the Almighty, All-Knowing"
  36,39,"As for the moon, We have ordained ˹precise˺ phases for it, until it ends up like an old, curved palm stalk"
  36,40,"It is not for the sun to catch up with the moon, nor does the night outrun the day. Each is travelling in an orbit of their own"
  36,41,Another sign for them is that We carried their ancestors ˹with Noah˺ in the fully loaded Ark
  36,42,and created for them similar things to ride in
  36,43,"If We willed, We could drown them: then no one would respond to their cries, nor would they be rescued—"
  36,44,"except by mercy from Us, allowing them enjoyment for a ˹little˺ while"
  36,45,"˹Still they turn away˺ when it is said to them, “Beware of what is ahead of you ˹in the Hereafter˺ and what is behind you ˹of destroyed nations˺ so you may be shown mercy.”"
  36,46,"Whenever a sign comes to them from their Lord, they turn away from it"
  36,47,"And when it is said to them, “Donate from what God has provided for you,” the disbelievers say to the believers, “Why should we feed those whom God could have fed if He wanted to? You are clearly astray!”"
  36,48,"And they ask ˹the believers˺, “When will this threat come to pass, if what you say is true?”"
  36,49,"They must be awaiting a single Blast, which will seize them while they are ˹entrenched˺ in ˹worldly˺ disputes"
  36,50,"Then they will not be able to make a ˹last˺ will, nor can they return to their own people"